  "prompt": "Can I use my laptop as a monitor? If so, how?",
  "response": "Yes, you can use your laptop as a monitor for another device like a gaming console, camera, or another computer. Here are a few methods:\n\n1. HDMI Input Method:\n- Some laptops have an HDMI input port (rare)\n- Connect the source device's HDMI output to your laptop's HDMI input\n- Change your laptop's display settings to show the external input\n\n2. Software Solutions:\n- SpaceDesk (Windows)\n- Duet Display (Windows/Mac)\n- LonelyScreen (Mac)\n- These allow you to use your laptop as a secondary display\n\n3. Wireless Methods:\n- Miracast for Windows devices\n- AirPlay for Apple devices\n- Screen mirroring apps for Android\n\n4. Capture Card Method:\n- Use an external capture card\n- Connect the source device to the capture card\n- Connect the capture card to your laptop via USB\n\nNote: Not all laptops support these methods natively. Check your laptop's specifications and ports to determine the best approach for your specific device.\n\nThe most reliable method depends on your laptop model and the device you want to display.",
